35:33.972 --> 35:35.434
[monitor beeping]

35:35.434 --> 35:37.522
WORKER: The whole building?
‐ I'm not sure. I'll check.

35:37.522 --> 35:39.692
Hello?
I'm trying to call out.

35:39.692 --> 35:42.322
NURSE: Give it a minute or two,
the generator will kick in.

35:42.322 --> 35:45.203
[overlapping chatter]

35:45.203 --> 35:48.418
<i>[intense music building]</i>

35:48.418 --> 35:50.129
<i>[musical crash]</i>

35:50.129 --> 35:53.387
TALL MAN: [distorted voice]
Did you like it?
Did you like it?

35:53.387 --> 35:55.599
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:55.599 --> 35:57.520
<i>[distorted audio]</i>
<i>Did you like it?</i>

35:57.520 --> 35:59.941
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:59.941 --> 36:01.318
<i>[distorted audio]</i>
<i>Did you like it?</i>

36:01.318 --> 36:03.365
ANNIE: [grunts]

36:03.365 --> 36:06.287
[panting]

36:06.287 --> 36:08.709
[gasping]

36:08.709 --> 36:13.427
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:13.427 --> 36:16.433
[panting]

36:19.522 --> 36:21.191
[shoes squeak]

36:23.029 --> 36:26.076
JAMAL: Anne?

36:26.076 --> 36:28.247
What are you doing?

36:28.247 --> 36:31.086
‐ [panting]
I just‐‐I fell and‐‐

36:31.086 --> 36:33.717
was... [panting]

36:33.717 --> 36:36.348
Four needs Zofran.

36:36.348 --> 36:39.729
The blackout really got to her,
so I need to get in.

36:39.729 --> 36:41.065
JAMAL: Well, security
will be here soon.

36:41.065 --> 36:42.526
‐ Security?

36:42.526 --> 36:44.989
‐ Dr. H left her override key
at home again.

36:44.989 --> 36:46.534
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:46.534 --> 36:48.162
NURSE: You know,
Dr. H has an override key.

36:48.162 --> 36:49.289
She'll bring you in.

36:49.289 --> 36:50.501
[panel beeps]

36:50.501 --> 36:52.880
<i>JAMAL: Anne?</i>
NADIA: Take what you need.

36:52.880 --> 36:55.427
JAMAL: Anne, are you okay?

36:55.427 --> 36:57.431
‐ Never mind.

36:57.431 --> 37:00.437
[panting]

37:00.437 --> 37:03.443
<i>[tense music]</i>

37:03.443 --> 37:09.664
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:10.958 --> 37:12.878
NADIA: Understaffed,
underpaid.

37:12.878 --> 37:14.632
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:14.632 --> 37:18.222
You know, I've been stuck on
overnights for the last week,

37:18.222 --> 37:20.394
I'm exhausted.

37:20.394 --> 37:23.400
[insects chirping distantly]

37:35.549 --> 37:38.555
[insects chirping]

37:38.555 --> 37:41.561
<i>[curious music]</i>

37:41.561 --> 37:48.575
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:51.831 --> 37:54.504
[microwave door shuts]

37:54.504 --> 38:01.518
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:13.458 --> 38:16.422
<i>[muffled heavy rock music</i>
<i>playing over speakers]</i>

38:16.422 --> 38:19.428
<i>[singer singing indistinctly]</i>

38:19.428 --> 38:24.647
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:24.647 --> 38:27.611
SINGER: ♪ Too hard too long ♪

38:27.611 --> 38:29.740
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:29.740 --> 38:32.746
<i>[singer continues</i>
<i>indistinctly]</i>

38:32.746 --> 38:35.919
♪ All over
just one more time ♪

38:35.919 --> 38:38.925
[gas gurgling]

38:38.925 --> 38:45.939
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:52.453 --> 38:55.459
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

38:55.459 --> 39:02.431
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:03.475 --> 39:06.481
[gravel crunching]

39:06.481 --> 39:09.487
[thunder rumbling]

39:09.487 --> 39:14.622
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:14.622 --> 39:17.628
[distant siren wailing]

39:17.628 --> 39:20.634
[siren swells, fades]

39:20.634 --> 39:27.648
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:46.602 --> 39:49.232
[floors creak]

39:51.904 --> 39:54.910
[objects rattling]

39:54.910 --> 39:58.292
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:58.292 --> 40:00.881
[cabinet door shuts]

40:00.881 --> 40:06.099
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:06.099 --> 40:08.020
‐ [inhales sharply]

40:08.020 --> 40:11.026
<i>[eerie, discordant music]</i>

40:11.026 --> 40:16.621
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:27.225 --> 40:29.772
[door creaking]

40:31.442 --> 40:38.330
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:38.330 --> 40:39.917
[car door slams]

40:39.917 --> 40:41.671
[car alarm chirps]

40:41.671 --> 40:43.341
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:43.341 --> 40:45.595
[panting]

40:45.595 --> 40:51.064
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:56.451 --> 40:58.746
[door handle rattles]

40:58.746 --> 41:00.584
[keys jingle, clatter]

41:00.584 --> 41:03.213
[door slams]
[latch clicks]

41:03.213 --> 41:04.967
[door creaks]

41:06.762 --> 41:09.477
ABDI: [yawns]

41:10.687 --> 41:13.025
[object clatters]

41:26.969 --> 41:33.983
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:50.600 --> 41:54.232
[glass shattering]
[flames roaring]

41:54.232 --> 41:57.698
[fire alarm beeping]

41:57.698 --> 42:03.166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:03.166 --> 42:06.089
[coughing]

42:06.089 --> 42:09.178
[beeping continues]

42:09.178 --> 42:13.061
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:13.061 --> 42:16.234
[glass shatters]

42:18.113 --> 42:20.242
[coughing]

42:20.242 --> 42:22.497
[extinguisher spraying]

42:22.497 --> 42:26.087
[engine rumbling]

42:26.087 --> 42:33.060
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:36.567 --> 42:38.488
[coughing]

42:41.661 --> 42:43.581
‐ [panting]

42:43.581 --> 42:45.585
[distant sirens wail]

42:49.593 --> 42:51.722
[phone ringing]

42:51.722 --> 42:53.893
<i>ANNOUNCER:</i>
<i>Eric Parker to the ER.</i>

42:53.893 --> 42:56.022
<i>Eric Parker to ER.</i>

42:56.022 --> 42:59.028
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

42:59.028 --> 43:06.042
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:11.177 --> 43:12.347
[car door slams]

43:12.347 --> 43:15.395
OFFICER: Ace Merrill?

43:15.395 --> 43:17.022
ACE: You know who I am.

43:17.022 --> 43:19.903
OFFICER: There was a fire
last night in Salem's Lot.

43:19.903 --> 43:21.866
Abdi and
Nadia Howlwadaag's house.

43:21.866 --> 43:23.494
Where were you last night?

43:23.494 --> 43:30.508
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:37.439 --> 43:39.610
[panel chirps]

43:39.610 --> 43:41.363
Can we come in and ask you
a couple of questions?

43:41.363 --> 43:43.033
ACE: Yeah, and I don't see
a fucking warrant.

43:43.033 --> 43:46.080
[indistinct radio chatter]

43:52.636 --> 43:54.723
[pills rattle]

43:54.723 --> 44:01.737
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:06.204 --> 44:07.999
‐ Hi, Doc.

44:09.628 --> 44:12.299
Just grabbing a Zofran for six.

44:12.299 --> 44:14.053
NADIA: Anne?
ANNIE: Mm‐hmm?

44:14.053 --> 44:17.602
NADIA: There's nobody in six.

44:17.602 --> 44:19.648
‐ I know that.

44:19.648 --> 44:21.944
I‐‐what I meant was
I was grabbing one for‐‐

44:21.944 --> 44:24.908
‐ Anne, stop.

44:24.908 --> 44:27.497
‐ Okay.

44:29.292 --> 44:30.545
I lost the chart.

44:30.545 --> 44:32.298
I forgot the rules‐‐
‐ What are you stealing?

44:32.298 --> 44:34.176
Oxycontin? Fentanyl?
‐ No!

44:34.176 --> 44:35.471
‐ You're an addict.
‐ No, no, no, I swear.

44:35.471 --> 44:36.932
NADIA: So you're selling
the drugs.
ANNE: No!

44:36.932 --> 44:38.561
‐ I'm gonna call the cops
if you don't tell me

44:38.561 --> 44:40.899
what you're doing here
right now.

44:40.899 --> 44:44.113
‐ [breathing heavily]

44:44.113 --> 44:45.783
I'm not right.

44:45.783 --> 44:48.623
[sighs]

44:48.623 --> 44:50.250
<i>[tense music]</i>

44:50.250 --> 44:54.258
I've got these things
in my mind.

44:54.258 --> 44:56.179
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:56.179 --> 45:00.103
<i>People running around</i>
<i>[stammers] and memories.</i>

45:00.103 --> 45:01.690
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:01.690 --> 45:04.404
I stumped 'em, though.

45:04.404 --> 45:07.076
The headshrinkers,
they couldn't diagnose me.

45:07.076 --> 45:10.082
They could not make me right,
but I found the recipe.

45:10.082 --> 45:12.587
‐ What recipe?

45:12.587 --> 45:16.512
‐ Risperdal, Haldol, Lithium.

45:16.512 --> 45:18.516
‐ Antipsychotics.

45:18.516 --> 45:20.770
You're stealing antipsychotics.

45:20.770 --> 45:22.022
Why?

45:22.022 --> 45:24.695
ANNIE: Because I can't‐‐
those go on my chart,

45:24.695 --> 45:27.032
the state association
sees that,

45:27.032 --> 45:30.873
I can't work in a hospital.

45:30.873 --> 45:33.253
I need my pills.

45:33.253 --> 45:35.007
[sniffs]

45:35.007 --> 45:38.764
Because Joy,
she needs the real me.

45:38.764 --> 45:42.021
<i>[baby crying]</i>
The right me.

45:42.021 --> 45:45.027
And the good Lord knows,
there's more to all of us,

45:45.027 --> 45:46.530
and not all of it's good

45:46.530 --> 45:49.703
but I am trying...

45:49.703 --> 45:51.749
for Joy.

45:51.749 --> 45:54.295
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:54.295 --> 45:55.965
‐ Joy is your daughter?

45:55.965 --> 45:58.554
ANNIE: I lost my own mom
when I was about her age,

45:58.554 --> 46:00.223
so I know‐‐

46:00.223 --> 46:02.562
I know how hard
it would be for her

46:02.562 --> 46:05.192
if I couldn't...
[breathing heavily]

46:05.192 --> 46:07.781
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:07.781 --> 46:09.451
NADIA: What are the doses?

46:09.451 --> 46:12.247
‐ What?
‐ Risperdal, Haldol, Lithium.

46:12.247 --> 46:14.461
How much?

46:15.880 --> 46:18.344
‐ 40, 20, 10.

46:18.344 --> 46:25.358
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:29.533 --> 46:33.791
NADIA:
Risper‐‐I'll have to make
a couple of small adjustments.

46:33.791 --> 46:36.672
We'll use samples
and off‐labels, but...

46:36.672 --> 46:40.220
you'll get what you need.

46:40.220 --> 46:42.559
[paper rustles]

46:42.559 --> 46:44.270
‐ The rules.

46:44.270 --> 46:46.065
NADIA: As long as you're
working at this hospital,

46:46.065 --> 46:47.610
I can cover you.

46:47.610 --> 46:51.660
ANNIE: But...why are you...

46:51.660 --> 46:54.248
‐ If more people took Lithium
and not Oxy,

46:54.248 --> 46:56.169
this would be
a much better world.

46:56.169 --> 47:00.678
But if you feel an episode
coming on, call me.

47:03.099 --> 47:04.603
‐ Thank you.

47:12.034 --> 47:13.662
‐ Where'd you find it?

47:13.662 --> 47:15.625
I thought I left
my key at home.

47:15.625 --> 47:17.670
‐ Behind your desk.

47:17.670 --> 47:19.591
It fell.

47:29.694 --> 47:32.700
<i>[soft music]</i>

47:32.700 --> 47:38.712
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:40.215 --> 47:45.518
CHRIS: Okay, and this
and, uh, your keys.

47:45.518 --> 47:52.532
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:59.838 --> 48:01.633
‐ So you got Old Bessie back?

48:01.633 --> 48:04.389
ANNIE: I did.

48:04.389 --> 48:06.435
‐ And some medicine?

48:09.399 --> 48:11.611
‐ Yes.

48:13.239 --> 48:15.995
‐ So we're leaving?

48:21.506 --> 48:25.348
‐ We're searchers, you and me.

48:25.348 --> 48:29.397
My dad, your grandpa‐‐
that good old guy,

48:29.397 --> 48:32.110
they don't make men like that,
little love‐‐not anymore.

48:32.110 --> 48:34.991
Now they just make dirty birds
and paper fakes.

48:34.991 --> 48:37.789
No heroes, no real men,
sorry to say.

48:37.789 --> 48:41.170
But my dad was one of them,
and he would say to me,

48:41.170 --> 48:44.928
"Annie, there are two kinds
of people that made America:

48:44.928 --> 48:47.099
searchers and settlers."

48:47.099 --> 48:49.938
He was a searcher,
Dad, your grandpa.

48:49.938 --> 48:52.568
He settled for nothing,
that one.

48:52.568 --> 48:56.325
And my mom, she was a settler.

48:56.325 --> 48:58.956
You set her down anywhere
and she would make a home.

48:58.956 --> 49:00.876
She would make it perfect,

49:00.876 --> 49:04.384
and she would keep
making it perfect until...

49:04.384 --> 49:06.430
<i>[nostalgic music]</i>

49:06.430 --> 49:09.644
Till it said uncle, you know?

49:09.644 --> 49:12.483
And me, well...

49:12.483 --> 49:16.031
I'm kind of a funny old
oogy mess of both.

49:16.031 --> 49:19.956
All mixed up sometimes,
but good things besides

49:19.956 --> 49:24.256
and always, always
your best interests
at heart, Joy.

49:24.256 --> 49:25.593
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:25.593 --> 49:29.057
See, I'm a searcher
who just wants to settle.

49:29.057 --> 49:31.187
Wants it bad.

49:31.187 --> 49:34.736
I just can't seem
to find a place to alight.

49:34.736 --> 49:37.240
Can't seem to find
that Laughing Place

49:37.240 --> 49:40.246
that'll live up to you...

49:40.246 --> 49:43.085
my perfection.

49:43.085 --> 49:45.883
I'm not saying this is it,
but I am saying

49:45.883 --> 49:49.641
you deserve a chance
to see‐‐to settle a little,

49:49.641 --> 49:52.355
make a place in the world.

49:52.355 --> 49:54.233
Maybe...

49:54.233 --> 49:58.324
anywhere could be
the Laughing Place
if we're there together.

49:58.324 --> 50:00.788
Even here.

50:00.788 --> 50:02.708
Maybe.

50:02.708 --> 50:05.339
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50:05.339 --> 50:07.593
Mm.

50:07.593 --> 50:14.607
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50:32.852 --> 50:34.564
‐ What's this for?

50:34.564 --> 50:37.319
‐ You've been cooped up
long enough.

50:37.319 --> 50:39.449
Why don't you go get yourself
some drawing paper?

50:39.449 --> 50:41.411
‐ [stammers]
By myself?

50:41.411 --> 50:44.333
‐ How else are you gonna
draw us up a better world?

50:44.333 --> 50:47.798
<i>♪ ♪</i>

51:03.121 --> 51:05.278
<i>ABDI:</i>
<i>[speaking foreign language]</i>

51:16.356 --> 51:18.485
<i>♪ ♪</i>

51:22.493 --> 51:24.789
‐ Ace did some KKK shit.

51:24.789 --> 51:26.418
Trying to burn us both alive.

51:26.418 --> 51:29.716
‐ Ace?
‐ Thank God you weren't here.

51:32.680 --> 51:35.686
NADIA: This has to stop, Abdi.

51:35.686 --> 51:37.230
ABDI: It will.

51:38.650 --> 51:41.196
Put that away!
Do not make things worse.

51:50.799 --> 51:53.304
[train horn blaring]

51:53.304 --> 51:56.352
[train wheels rumbling]

52:19.064 --> 52:21.444
<i>REPORTER: With the 400th</i>
<i>anniversary approaching,</i>

52:21.444 --> 52:23.239
<i>rumors that</i>
<i>witch trials happened</i>

52:23.239 --> 52:24.951
<i>near this part</i>
<i>of Salem's Lot abound,</i>

52:24.951 --> 52:27.665
<i>but that hasn't stop</i>
<i>construction.</i>

52:27.665 --> 52:29.627
<i>It may not</i>
<i>look like much yet,</i>

52:29.627 --> 52:31.631
<i>but once the foundation</i>
<i>is poured tomorrow,</i>

52:31.631 --> 52:34.679
<i>rest assured, the new</i>
<i>Somali mall will rise up‐‐</i>

52:34.679 --> 52:36.516
<i>[bright orchestral music]</i>
<i>‐ Change your language.</i>

52:36.516 --> 52:39.104
<i>[TV continues indistinctly]</i>

52:39.104 --> 52:41.275
[keys jingling]
[doorknob rattling]

52:41.275 --> 52:43.112
ANNIE: Joy?

52:43.112 --> 52:45.409
ACE: Your daughter here?

52:47.913 --> 52:50.377
‐ What are you doing
in my house?

52:50.377 --> 52:52.590
[ice cream plops slowly]

52:52.590 --> 52:54.969
‐ You're dripping.

52:59.729 --> 53:03.027
She gets out at night,
that kid.

53:03.027 --> 53:06.283
Gets out...

53:06.283 --> 53:08.997
gets into shit.

53:08.997 --> 53:11.001
Other people's shit.

53:14.342 --> 53:15.552
ANNIE: Get out.

53:15.552 --> 53:18.307
‐ You've heard of
"landlord may enter"?

53:18.307 --> 53:21.522
That's state law.
I'm the landlord.

53:21.522 --> 53:24.194
I may enter.

53:24.194 --> 53:26.574
Landlord's gotta do
his own background checks.

53:26.574 --> 53:30.707
You're not the first lammer
showed up here paying cash,

53:30.707 --> 53:34.297
driving around
with fictitious plates.

53:36.427 --> 53:38.097
‐ I'll call the police.

53:38.097 --> 53:42.773
‐ See, Anne Ingalls
from Pepin, Wisconsin

53:42.773 --> 53:45.194
just might do that.

53:45.194 --> 53:49.537
But Annie Wilkes
from Bakersfield, California

53:49.537 --> 53:52.751
sure as shit would not.

53:52.751 --> 53:56.801
I'm happy to provide
free internet access
to all our guests

53:56.801 --> 54:00.141
as long as I get to ride along.

54:00.141 --> 54:04.525
So here's the deal,
Annie Wilkes...

54:06.194 --> 54:09.618
Your daughter saw some shit
she shouldn't have,

54:09.618 --> 54:12.165
so you're gonna shut her up,
so I don't have‐‐

54:12.165 --> 54:14.252
‐ [yelps]
‐ [groans]

54:14.252 --> 54:16.340
[muffled gagging]

54:16.340 --> 54:18.803
‐ [yelping]

54:18.803 --> 54:20.515
‐ [gagging]

54:20.515 --> 54:23.438
‐ [grunting]

54:23.438 --> 54:26.527
‐ [gagging]

54:26.527 --> 54:29.282
‐ [whimpering]

54:29.282 --> 54:31.996
‐ [groans, gagging]

54:33.374 --> 54:36.380
[gurgling]
‐ [whimpering]

54:37.925 --> 54:40.931
‐ [groaning]

54:43.436 --> 54:46.442
ANNIE: [panting]

54:53.330 --> 54:56.337
‐ [muffled breathing]

54:56.337 --> 54:59.300
<i>[dark music]</i>

54:59.300 --> 55:04.018
<i>♪ ♪</i>

55:04.018 --> 55:06.440
[groaning]

55:06.440 --> 55:13.454
<i>♪ ♪</i>

55:19.383 --> 55:21.554
[exhales sharply]

55:21.554 --> 55:25.395
<i>♪ ♪</i>

55:25.395 --> 55:26.606
[bones crunch]

55:26.606 --> 55:29.277
[squelching]

55:29.277 --> 55:36.291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

55:48.816 --> 55:51.822
<i>[tense music building]</i>

55:51.822 --> 55:55.413
<i>♪ ♪</i>

56:00.757 --> 56:03.429
‐ Mom?

56:03.429 --> 56:08.271
SINGER: ♪ Let the river run ♪

56:08.271 --> 56:11.988
♪ Let all the dreamers ♪

56:11.988 --> 56:16.037
♪ Wake the nation ♪

56:16.037 --> 56:18.041
♪ Come ♪

56:18.041 --> 56:23.970
♪ The New Jerusalem ♪

56:23.970 --> 56:25.598
<i>♪ ♪</i>

56:25.598 --> 56:29.606
♪ Silver cities rise ♪

56:29.606 --> 56:32.696
♪ The morning lights ♪

56:32.696 --> 56:35.702
♪ The streets that meet them ♪

56:35.702 --> 56:39.835
♪ And sirens call them on ♪

56:39.835 --> 56:43.634
♪ With a song ♪

56:43.634 --> 56:45.388
[engine turns over]

56:45.388 --> 56:50.607
♪ It's asking for the taking ♪

56:50.607 --> 56:52.903
♪ Trembling ♪

56:52.903 --> 56:55.867
♪ Shaking ♪

56:55.867 --> 57:00.710
♪ Oh, my heart is aching ♪

57:00.710 --> 57:03.841
♪ We're coming to the edge,
running on the water ♪

57:03.841 --> 57:06.430
♪ Coming through the fog,
your sons and daughters ♪

57:06.430 --> 57:10.897
♪ We the great and small ♪

57:10.897 --> 57:13.318
♪ Stand on a star ♪

